our%20account%20before%20the%20term%20ends.%20But%20with%20a%20no-penalty%20CD%2C%20you%20won't%20have%20to%20pay%20an%20early%20withdrawal%20penalty.%20The%20best%20no-penalty%20CDs%20will%20offer%20rates%20slightly%20higher%20than%20the%20best%20high-yield%20savings%20accounts%2C%20and%20can%20offer%20a%20substantially%20improved%20interest%20rate%20over%20traditional%20brick-and-mortar%20savings%20accounts.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch3%3E6-Month%20CDs%3C%2Fh3%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Fbanking%2Fbest-6-month-cd-rates%5C%22%3Ebest%206-month%20CDs%3C%2Fa%3E%20are%20offering%20interest%20rates%20in%20the%20mid-5%25%20range.%20Six-month%20CDs%20are%20best%20for%20those%20who%20are%20looking%20for%20elevated%20rates%20on%20their%20savings%20for%20short-term%20gains%2C%20but%20are%20uncomfortable%20having%20limited%20access%20to%20their%20cash%20in%20the%20long%20term.%20These%20can%20be%20a%20good%20option%20for%20those%20who%20may%20just%20be%20getting%20started%20with%20saving%2C%20or%20who%20don't%20have%20a%20large%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Fbanking%2Fwhat-is-an-emergency-fund%5C%22%3Eemergency%20fund%3C%2Fa%3E%20for%20unexpected%20expenses.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch3%3E1-Year%20CDs%3C%2Fh3%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Fbanking%2Fbest-1-year-cd-rates%5C%22%3Ebest%201-year%20CDs%3C%2Fa%3E%20tend%20to%20offer%20some%20of%20the%20top%20CD%20rates%2C%20and%20are%20a%20popular%20option%20for%20many%20investors.%20A%201-year%20term%20can%20be%20an%20attractive%20option%20for%20someone%20building%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Fbanking%2Fcd-ladder%5C%22%3ECD%20ladder%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20or%20for%20someone%20who%20has%20a%20reasonable%20cash%20safety%20net%20but%20is%20still%20concerned%20about%20long-term%20expenses.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch3%3E2-Year%20CDs%3C%2Fh3%3E%3Cp%