nt.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20charges%20were%20dropped%20and%20they%20were%20free%20to%20contest%20an%20election%20the%20following%20year.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHasina%20won%20in%20a%20landslide%20and%20has%20been%20in%20power%20ever%20since.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%2078-year-old%20Zia%20meanwhile%20is%20in%20ailing%20health%20and%20confined%20to%20hospital%20after%20graft%20charges%20saw%20her%20sentenced%20to%20a%2017-year%20prison%20term%20in%202018%2C%20with%20top%20leaders%20from%20her%20party%20also%20behind%20bars.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHasina%20has%20been%20praised%20by%20supporters%20for%20leading%20Bangladesh%20through%20a%20remarkable%20economic%20boom%2C%20largely%20on%20the%20back%20of%20the%20mostly%20female%20factory%20workforce%20powering%20its%20garment%20export%20industry.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBangladesh%2C%20one%20of%20the%20world's%20poorest%20countries%20when%20it%20gained%20independence%20from%20Pakistan%20in%201971%2C%20has%20grown%20an%20average%20of%20more%20than%20six%20percent%20each%20year%20since%202009.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EPoverty%20has%20plummeted%20and%20more%20than%2095%20percent%20of%20the%20country's%20170%20million%20people%20now%20have%20access%20to%20electricity%2C%20with%20per%20capita%20income%20overtaking%20India%20in%202021.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHasina%20also%20received%20international%20acclaim%20for%20opening%20Bangladesh's%20doors%20to%20hundreds%20of%20thousands%20of%20Rohingya%20refugees%20fleeing%20a%202017%20military%20crackdown%20in%20neighbouring%20Myanmar.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAnd%20she%20has%20been%20hailed%20for%20a%20decisive%20crackdown%20on%20Islamist%20militants%20in%20the%20Muslim-majority%20nation%20after%20five%20homegrown%20extremists%20stormed%20a%20Dhaka%20cafe%20popular%20with%20Western%20expatriates%20and%20killed%2022%20people%20in%202016.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3E-%20Silencing%20dissent%20-%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBut%20her%20government's%20intolerance%20towards%20dissent%20has%20gi