F's%20history%20and%20is%20set%20for%20an%20August%2015%2C%202024%2C%20release%20in%20multiple%20languages.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22Jigar%20Shah%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fentertainment%2Fhindi%2Fbollywood%2Fnews%2Fthangalaan-makers-to-host-a-special-screening-for-kgf-star-yash-exclusive%2Farticleshow%2F112285822.cms%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22He%20says%20AI%20can%20tell%20your%20politics%20and%20sexuality%20by%20reading%20your%20face.%20Is%20he%20right%3F%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%223600%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22An%20AI%20figure%20scanning%20a%20phone%20displaying%20an%20individual%20figure%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F66aa4e66aab37011780bfafa%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221800%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3E%3Cp%3EBrian%20Stauffer%20for%20BI%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EMichal%20Kosinski%20knows%20exactly%20how%20he%20sounds%20when%20he%20talks%20about%20his%20research.%20And%20how%20it%20sounds%20is%20not%20great.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20psychologist%20at%20Stanford%20University%2C%20Kosinski%20is%20a%20specialist%20in%20psychometrics%20%E2%80%94%20a%20field%20that%20attempts%20to%20measure%20the%20facets%20of%20the%20human%20mind.%20For%20more%20than%20a%20decade%2C%20his%20work%20has%20freaked%20people%20right%20the%20hell%20out.%20In%20study%20after%20study%2C%20Kosinski%20has%20made%20scarily%20plausible%20claims%20that%20machine-learning%20algorithms%20of%20artificial%20intelligence%20can%20discern%20deeply%20private%20things%20about%20us%20%E2%80%94%20our%20intelligence%2C%20our%20sexual%20preferences%2C%20our%20political%20beliefs%20%E2%80%94%20using%20little%20more%20than%20our%20Facebook%20likes%20and%20photographs%20of%20our%20faces.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI'm%20not%20even%20interested%20in%20faces%2C%26quot%3B%20Kosinski%20insists.%20%26quot%3BThere%20was%20nothing%20in%20my%20career%20that%20indicated%20I'd%20be%20spending%20a%20few%20years%20looking%20at%20people's%20appearances.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhat%20Kosinski%20cares%20about%20are%20data%20and%20psychology.%20And%20what%20are%20photographs%20if%20not%20pixelated%20data%3F%20%26quot%3BPsychological%20theory%20kind%20of%20shouts%20in%20your%20face%20that%20there%20should%20be%20links%20between%20facial%20appearance%20and%20intimate%20traits%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20says.%20That's%20why%20he%20believes%20that%20you%20can%20judge%20our%20inner%20lives%20by%20our%20outward%20characteristics.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt's%20a%20belief%20with%20disturbing%20implications.%20Science%20has%20been%20trying%20to%20divine%20truths%20about%20personality%20and%20behavior%20from%20various%20tests%20and%20images%20for%20centuries.%20As%20far%20back%20as%20the%201700s%2C%20physiognomists%20measured%20facial%20features%20in%20a%20search%20for%20ineffable%20qualities%20like%20nobility%20and%20immorality.%20Phrenologists%20used%20calipers%20to%20measure%20bumps%20on%20people's%20heads%2C%20hoping%20to%20diagnose%20mental%20incapacities%20or%20moral%20deficiencies.%20Eugenicists%20used%20photographs%20and%20IQ%20tests%20to%20determine%20which%20people%20were%20%26quot%3Binferior%2C%26quot%3B%20and%20sterilized%20those%20who%20didn't%20measure%20up%20%E2%80%94%20which%20usually%20turned%20out%20to%20be%20anyone%20who%20wasn't%20white%20and%20rich.%20The%20methods%20differed%2C%20but%20the%20underlying%20theory%20remained%20the%20same%3A%20that%20measurements%20could%20somehow%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Egauge%20the%20mind%2C%20and%20a%20person's%20value%20to%20society.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETo%20be%20clear%2C%20none%20of%20these%20%26quot%3Bsciences%26quot%3B%20worked.%20In%20fact%2C%20every%20time%20someone%20claimed%20they'd%20found%20a%20way%20to%20measure%20people's%20inner%20traits%20based%20on%20their%20exterior%20features%2C%20it%20quickly%20turned%20into%20a%20tool%20to%20discriminate%20against%20people%20based%20on%20their%20race%20or%20gender.%20That's%20because%20findings%20involving%20individuals%20almost%20always%20get%20applied%20to%20entire%20populations.%20It's%20a%20short%20leap%20from%20saying%20%26quot%3Bsome%20people%20are%20smarter%20than%20others%26quot%3B%20to%20%26quot%3B%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fap-scholar-who-sees-race-intelligence-ties-to-speak-at-harvard-2017-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Esome%20races%20are%20smarter%20than%20others%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E.%26quot%3B%20A%20test%20can%20be%20useful%20to%20assess%20which%20calculus%20class%20your%20daughter%20has%20an%20aptitude%20for.%20But%20it's%20malicious%20and%20wrong%20to%20use%20those%20test%20results%20to%20assert%20that%20there%20aren't%20many%20female%20software%20engineers%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.wired.com%2Fstory%2Fthe-pernicious-science-of-james-damores-google-memo%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Ebecause%20girls%20don't%20like%20math%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Yet%20today%2C%20intelligence%20testing%20and%20facial%20recognition%20continue%20to%20be%20used%2C%20and%20abused%2C%20in%20everything%20from%20marketing%20and%20job%20hiring%20to%20college%20admissions%20and%20law%20enforcement.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EKosinski%20is%20aware%20of%20the%20long%2C%20dark%20history%20of%20his%20chosen%20field.%20Like%20his%20skull-measuring%20forebears%2C%20he%20believes%20that%20his%20research%20is%20%3Cem%3Eright%20%E2%80%94%20%3C%2Fem%3Ethat%20AI%2C%20combined%20with%20facial%20recognition%2C%20can%20lay%20bare%20our%20personalities%20and%20preferences%20more%20accurately%20than%20humans%20can.%20And%20to%20him%2C%20that%20accuracy%20is%20what%20makes%20his%20findings%20so%20dangerous.%20In%20pursuit%20of%20this%20ability%2C%20he%20fears%2C%20its%20creators%20will%20violate%20people's%20privacy%20and%20use%20it%20to%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Emanipulate%20public%20opinion%20and%20persecute%20minority%20groups.%20His%20work%2C%20he%20says%2C%20isn't%20meant%20to%20be%20used%20as%20a%20tool%20of%20oppression%2C%20like%20the%20pseudoscience%20of%20the%20past.%20It's%20meant%20as%20a%20warning%20about%20the%20future.%20In%20a%20sense%2C%20he's%20the%20Oppenheimer%20of%20AI%2C%20warning%20us%20all%20about%20the%20destructive%20potential%20of%20an%20artificial-intelligence%20bomb%20%E2%80%94%20while%20he's%20building%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BVery%20soon%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20says%2C%20%26quot%3Bwe%20may%20find%20ourselves%20in%20a%20position%20where%20these%20models%20have%20properties%20and%20capacities%20that%20are%20way%20ahead%20of%20what%20humans%20could%20dream%20of.%20And%20we%20will%20not%20even%20notice.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20we%20meet%2C%20Kosinski%20does%20not%20brandish%20any%20calipers%20to%20assess%20my%20brow%20and%20determine%20my%20tendency%20toward%20indolence%2C%20as%20the%20phrenologists%20of%20the%2019th%20century%20did.%20Instead%2C%20dressed%20in%20a%20California-casual%20flowered%20shirt%20and%20white%20leather%20loafers%20%E2%80%94%20no%20socks%20%E2%80%94%20he%20leads%20me%20to%20a%20sunny%20Stanford%20courtyard%20for%20coffee.%20We're%20surrounded%20by%20a%20happy%20and%20diverse%20crowd%20of%20business-school%20students.%20Here%2C%20on%20a%20perfect%20California%20day%2C%20he%20lays%20out%20the%20case%20for%20what%20he%20fears%20will%20be%20the%20secret%20algorithmic%20domination%20of%20our%20world.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBefore%20he%20worked%20with%20photographs%2C%20Kosinski%20was%20interested%20in%20Facebook.%20When%20he%20was%20a%20doctoral%20student%20at%20Cambridge%20in%20the%20mid-2000s%2C%20the%20few%20social%20scientists%20who%20took%20the%20emerging%20online%20world%20seriously%20regarded%20it%20as%20an%20uncanny%20valley%2C%20a%20place%20where%20people%20essentially%20donned%20fake%20personalities.%20How%20they%20behaved%20online%20didn't%20reflect%20their%20psychology%20or%20behavior%20in%20the%20real%20world.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EKosinski%20disagreed.%20%26quot%3BI%20felt%20that%20I'm%20still%20myself%20while%20using%20those%20products%20and%20services%2C%20and%20that%20my%20friends%20and%20people%20I%20knew%20were%20like%20this%20as%20well%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20says.%20Even%20people%20pretending%20to%20be%20dwarf%20paladins%20or%20sex%20dragons%20still%20had%20the%20same%20anxieties%2C%20biases%2C%20and%20prejudices%20they%20carried%20around%20IRL.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMuch%20to%20the%20dismay%20of%20his%20thesis%20advisor%2C%20this%20became%20the%20foundation%20of%20Kosinski's%20approach.%20%26quot%3BThat%20was%20the%20first%20aim%2C%20to%20show%20that%20continuity%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20says.%20%26quot%3BAnd%20that%20led%20me%20to%20the%20second%20aim%2C%20which%20was%3A%20If%20we%20are%20all%20still%20ourselves%20online%2C%20that%20means%20we%20can%20use%20data%20collected%20online%20%E2%80%94%20Big%20Data%20%E2%80%94%20to%20understand%20humans%20better.%26quot%3B%20To%20test%20his%20hypothesis%2C%20Kosinski%20and%20a%20grad%20student%20named%20David%20Stillwell%20at%20the%20Cambridge%20Psychometrics%20Centre%20created%20a%20Facebook%20app%20called%20myPersonality%20%E2%80%94%20an%20old-school%20magazine-style%20quiz%20that%20tested%20for%20personality%20traits%20like%20%26quot%3Bopenness%26quot%3B%20or%20%26quot%3Bintroversion%26quot%3B%20while%20also%20hoovering%20up%20people's%20Facebook%20likes.%20Then%20they%20built%20a%20computer%20model%20that%20mapped%20those%20likes%20to%20specific%20personality%20traits%20for%20nearly%2060%2C000%20people.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPublished%20in%20the%20Proceedings%20of%20the%20National%20Academy%20of%20Sciences%20in%202013%2C%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22http%3A%2F%2Fwww.pnas.org%2Fcgi%2Fdoi%2F10.1073%2Fpnas.1218772110%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Eresults%20seemed%20astonishing%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Facebook%20likes%20alone%20could%20predict%20someone's%20religion%20and%20politics%20with%20better%20than%2080%25%20accuracy.%20The%20model%20could%20tell%20whether%20a%20man%20was%20gay%20with%2088%25%20accuracy.%20Sometimes%20the%20algorithm%20didn't%20seem%20to%20have%20any%20particularly%20magical%20powers%20%E2%80%94%20liking%20the%20musical%20%26quot%3BWicked%2C%26quot%3B%20for%20example%2C%20was%20a%20leading%20predictor%20of%20male%20homosexuality.%20But%20other%20connections%20were%20baffling.%20Among%20the%20best%20predictors%20of%20high%20intelligence%2C%20for%20instance%2C%20were%20liking%20%26quot%3Bthunderstorms%26quot%3B%20and%20%26quot%3Bcurly%20fries.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHow%20did%20the%20machine%20draw%20such%20seemingly%20accurate%20conclusions%20from%20such%20arbitrary%20data%3F%20%26quot%3BWho%20knows%20why%3F%26quot%3B%20Stillwell%2C%20now%20the%20director%20of%20the%20Psychometrics%20Centre%2C%20tells%20me.%20%26quot%3BWho%20cares%20why%3F%20If%20it's%20a%20group%20of%2010%2C000%20individuals%2C%20the%20mistakes%20cancel%20out%2C%20and%20it's%20good%20enough%20for%20a%20population.%26quot%3B%20Stillwell%20and%20Kosinski%2C%20in%20other%20words%2C%20aren't%20particularly%20interested%20in%20whether%20their%20models%20say%20anything%20about%20actual%20causation%2C%20about%20an%20explanation%20behind%20the%20connections.%20Correlation%20is%20enough.%20Their%20method%20enabled%20a%20machine%20to%20predict%20human%20behaviors%20and%20preferences.%20They%20don't%20have%20to%20know%20%E2%80%94%20or%20even%20care%20%E2%80%94%20how.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%223277%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22An%20individual%20trapped%20by%20an%20eye%20shaped%20trap%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F66aa4fcdaab37011780bfbb1%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222400%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3E%3Cp%3EBrian%20Stauffer%20for%20BI%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20didn't%20take%20long%20for%20such%20models%20to%20be%20weaponized.%20Another%20researcher%20at%20the%20Psychometrics%20Centre%2C%20Aleksandr%20Kogan%2C%20took%20similar%20ideas%20to%20a%20political-campaign%20consultancy%20called%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcambridge-analytica-a-guide-to-the-trump-linked-data-firm-that-harvested-50-million-facebook-profiles-2018-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3ECambridge%20Analytica%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20which%20sold%20its%20services%20to%20the%202016%20campaign%20of%20Donald%20Trump%20and%20to%20Brexit%20advocates%20in%20the%20UK.%20Did%20the%20efforts%20to%20manipulate%20social-media%20feeds%20and%20change%20voting%20behaviors%20actually%20influence%20those%20votes%3F%20No%20one%20knows%20for%20sure.%20But%20a%20year%20later%2C%20Stillwell%20and%20Kosinski%20used%20myPersonality%20data%20to%20create%20psychologically%20customized%20ads%20that%20markedly%20influenced%20what%203.5%20million%20people%20bought%20online%2C%20versus%20those%20who%20saw%20ads%20that%20weren't%20targeted%20to%20them.%20The%20research%20was%20at%20the%20forefront%20of%20what%20is%20today%20commonplace%3A%20using%20social-media%20algorithms%20to%20sell%20us%20stuff%20based%20on%20our%20every%20point%20and%20click.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3EAround%20the%20same%20time%20Kosinski%20was%20demonstrating%20that%20his%20research%20could%20manipulate%20online%20shoppers%2C%20a%20bunch%20of%20companies%20were%20starting%20to%20sell%20facial-recognition%20systems.%20At%20the%20time%2C%20the%20systems%20weren't%20even%20good%20at%20what%20they%20claimed%20to%20do%3A%20distinguishing%20among%20individuals%20for%20identification%20purposes.%20But%20Kosinski%20wondered%20whether%20software%20could%20use%20the%20data%20embedded%20in%20huge%20numbers%20of%20photographs%2C%20the%20same%20way%20it%20had%20with%20Facebook%20likes%2C%20to%20discern%20things%20like%20emotions%20and%20personality%20traits.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMost%20scientists%20consider%20that%20idea%20a%20form%20of%20modern%20physiognomy%20%E2%80%94%20a%20pseudoscience%20based%20on%20the%20mistaken%20assumption%20that%20our%20faces%20reveal%20something%20about%20our%20minds.%20Sure%2C%20we%20can%20tell%20a%20lot%20about%20someone%20by%20looking%20at%20them.%20At%20a%20glance%20we%20can%20guess%2C%20with%20a%20fair%20degree%20of%20accuracy%2C%20things%20like%20age%2C%20gender%2C%20and%20race.%20Based%20on%20simple%20odds%2C%20we%20can%20intuit%20that%20an%20older%20white%20man%20is%20more%20likely%20to%20be%20politically%20conservative%20than%20a%20younger%20Latina%20woman%3B%20an%20unshaven%20guy%20in%20a%20filthy%20hoodie%20and%20demolished%20sneakers%20probably%20has%20less%20ready%20cash%20than%20a%20woman%20in%20a%20Chanel%20suit.%20But%20discerning%20stuff%20like%20extroversion%2C%20or%20intelligence%2C%20or%20trustworthiness%3F%20Come%20on.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20once%20again%2C%20Kosinski%20believed%20that%20a%20machine%2C%20relying%20on%20Big%20Data%2C%20could%20divine%20our%20souls%20from%20our%20faces%20in%20a%20way%20that%20humans%20can't.%20People%20judge%20you%20based%20on%20your%20face%2C%20he%20says%2C%20and%20treat%20you%20differently%20based%20on%20those%20judgments.%20That%2C%20in%20turn%2C%20changes%20your%20psychology.%20If%20people%20constantly%20reward%20you%20with%20jobs%20and%20invitations%20to%20parties%20because%20they%20consider%20you%20attractive%2C%20that%20will%20alter%20your%20character%20over%20time.%20Your%20face%20affects%20how%20people%20treat%20you%2C%20and%20how%20people%20treat%20you%20affects%20who%20you%20are.%20All%20he%20needed%20was%20an%20algorithm%20to%20read%20the%20clues%20written%20on%20our%20faces%20%E2%80%94%20to%20separate%20the%20curly%20fries%20from%20the%20Broadway%20musicals.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EKosinski%20and%20a%20colleague%20scraped%20a%20dating%20site%20for%20photographs%20of%2036%2C360%20men%20and%2038%2C593%20women%2C%20equally%20divided%20between%20gay%20and%20straight%20(as%20indicated%20by%20their%20%26quot%3Blooking%20for%26quot%3B%20fields).%20Then%20he%20used%20a%20facial-recognition%20algorithm%20called%20VGG-Face%2C%20trained%20on%202.6%20million%20images%2C%20to%20compare%20his%20test%20subjects%20based%20on%20500%20variables.%20Presenting%20the%20model%20with%20photographs%20in%20pairs%20%E2%80%94%20one%20gay%20person%20and%20one%20straight%20person%20%E2%80%94%20he%20asked%20it%20to%20pick%20which%20one%20was%20gay.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPresented%20with%20at%20least%20five%20photographs%20of%20a%20person%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fpsycnet.apa.org%2Fdoi%2F10.1037%2Fpspa0000098%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3EKosinski's%20model%20picked%20the%20gay%20person%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20out%20of%20a%20pair%20with%2091%25%20accuracy.%20Humans%2C%20by%20contrast%2C%20were%20right%20only%2061%25%20of%20the%20time.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20paper%20gestures%20at%20an%20explanation%20%E2%80%94%20hormonal%20exposure%20in%20the%20womb%20something%20something.%20But%20once%20again%2C%20Kosinski%20isn't%20really%20interested%20in%20%3Cem%3Ewhy%20%3C%2Fem%3Ethe%20model%20works.%20To%20him%2C%20what's%20important%20is%20that%20a%20computer%20trained%20on%20thousands%20of%20images%20can%20draw%20accurate%20conclusions%20about%20something%20like%20sexual%20preference%20by%20combining%20multiple%20invisible%20details%20about%20a%20person.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOthers%20disagreed.%20Researchers%20who%20study%20faces%20and%20emotions%20criticized%20both%20his%20math%20and%20his%20conclusions.%20The%20Guardian%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.theguardian.com%2Ftechnology%2F2018%2Fjul%2F07%2Fartificial-intelligence-can-tell-your-sexuality-politics-surveillance-paul-lewis%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Etook%20Kosinski%20to%20task%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20for%20giving%20a%20talk%20about%20his%20work%20in%20famously%20homophobic%20Russia.%20The%20Economist%20called%20his%20research%20%26quot%3B%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.economist.com%2Fscience-and-technology%2F2017%2F09%2F09%2Fadvances-in-ai-are-used-to-spot-signs-of-sexuality%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Ebad%20news%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%26quot%3B%20for%20anyone%20with%20secrets.%20The%20Human%20Rights%20Campaign%20and%20GLAAD%20issued%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.theguardian.com%2Fworld%2F2017%2Fsep%2F08%2Fai-gay-gaydar-algorithm-facial-recognition-criticism-stanford%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Estatement%20decrying%20the%20study%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20warning%20that%20it%20could%20be%20used%20by%20brutal%20regimes%20to%20persecute%20gay%20people.%20%26quot%3BStanford%20should%20distance%20itself%20from%20such%20junk%20science%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20HRC%20said%2C%20%26quot%3Brather%20than%20lending%20its%20name%20and%20credibility%20to%20research%20that%20is%20dangerously%20flawed%20and%20leaves%20the%20world%20%E2%80%94%20and%20this%20case%2C%20millions%20of%20people's%20lives%20%E2%80%94%20worse%20and%20less%20safe%20than%20before.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EKosinski%20felt%20blindsided.%20%26quot%3BPeople%20said%2C%20'Stanford%20professor%20developed%20facial-recognition%20algorithms%20to%20build%20a%20gaydar.'%20But%20I%20don't%20even%20actually%20care%20about%20facial%20appearance%20per%20se.%20I%20care%20about%20privacy%2C%20and%20the%20algorithmic%20power%20to%20do%20stuff%20that%20we%20humans%20cannot%20do.%26quot%3B%20He%20wasn't%20trying%20to%20build%20a%20scanner%20for%20right-wingers%20to%20take%20to%20school-board%20meetings%2C%20he%20says.%20He%20wanted%20policymakers%20to%20take%20action%2C%20and%20gay%20people%20to%20prepare%20themselves%20for%20the%20world%20to%20come.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20did%20not%20create%20a%20privacy-invading%20tool%2C%20but%20rather%20showed%20that%20basic%20and%20widely%20used%20methods%20pose%20serious%20privacy%20threats%2C%26quot%3B%20Kosinski%20and%20his%20coauthor%20wrote%20in%20their%20paper.%20%26quot%3BWe%20hope%20that%20our%20findings%20will%20inform%20the%20public%20and%20policymakers%2C%20and%20inspire%20them%20to%20design%20technologies%20and%20write%20policies%20that%20reduce%20the%20risks%20faced%20by%20homosexual%20communities%20across%20the%20world.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3EKosinski%20kept%20at%20it.%20This%20time%2C%20he%20scraped%20more%20than%20a%20million%20photographs%20of%20people%20from%20Facebook%20and%20a%20dating%20site%2C%20along%20with%20the%20political%20affiliations%20they%20listed%20in%20their%20profiles.%20Using%20VGGFace2%20%E2%80%94%20open%20source%2C%20available%20to%20anyone%20who%20wants%20to%20try%20such%20a%20thing%20%E2%80%94%20he%20converted%20those%20faces%20to%20thousands%20of%20data%20points%20and%20averaged%20together%20the%20data%20for%20liberals%20and%20conservatives.%20Then%20he%20showed%20a%20new%20algorithm%20hundreds%20of%20thousands%20of%20pairs%20of%20images%20from%20the%20dating%20site%20and%20asked%20it%20to%20separate%20the%20MAGA%20lovers%20from%20the%20Bernie%20bros.%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Faffiliate.insider.com%3Fh%3D4cda1e4dd037b0fe45ef3fc4d819d320e8836b43431fcebf44defa69c10848bd%26postID%3D6679c25985b49b35b27e1ffa%26postSlug%3Doppenheimer-artificial-intelligence-michal-kosinski-predict-facial-recognition-2024-7%26site%3Dbi%26u%3Dhttps%253A%252F%252Fwww.nature.com%252Farticles%252Fs41598-020-79310-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3EThe%20machine%20got%20it%20right%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%2072%25%20of%20the%20time.%20In%20pairs%20matched%20for%20age%2C%20gender%2C%20and%20race%20%E2%80%94%20knocking%20out%20the%20easy%20cues%20%E2%80%94%20accuracy%20fell%2C%20but%20only%20by%20a%20little.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20might%20seem%20like%20a%20big%20scary%20deal.%20AI%20can%20tell%20if%20we%20have%20political%20wrongthink!%20It%20can%20tricorder%20our%20sexuality!%20But%20most%20people%20who%20study%20faces%20and%20personality%20think%20Kosinski%20is%20flat-out%20wrong.%20%26quot%3BI%20absolutely%20do%20not%20dispute%20the%20fact%20that%20you%20can%20design%20an%20algorithm%20that%20can%20guess%20much%20better%20than%20chance%20whether%20a%20person%20is%20gay%20or%20straight%2C%26quot%3B%20says%20Alexander%20Todorov%2C%20a%20psychologist%20at%20the%20University%20of%20Chicago.%20%26quot%3BBut%20that's%20because%20all%20of%20the%20images%20are%20posted%20by%20the%20users%20themselves%2C%20so%20there%20are%20lots%20of%20confounds.%26quot%3B%20Kosinski's%20model%2C%20in%20other%20words%2C%20isn't%20picking%20up%20microscopically%20subtle%20cues%20from%20the%20photos.%20It's%20just%20picking%20up%20on%20the%20way%20gay%20people%20present%20themselves%20on%20dating%20sites%20%E2%80%94%20which%2C%20not%20surprisingly%2C%20is%20often%20%3Cem%3Every%20%3C%2Fem%3Edifferent%20from%20the%20way%20straight%20people%20present%20themselves%20to%20potential%20partners.%20Control%20for%20that%20in%20the%20photos%2C%20and%20the%20algorithmic%20gaydar's%20accuracy%20ends%20up%20little%20better%20than%20chance.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EKosinski%20has%20tried%20to%20respond%20to%20these%20critiques.%20In%20his%20most%20recent%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fdoi.apa.org%2Fdoi%2F10.1037%2Famp0001295%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Estudy%20on%20political%20affiliation%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20he%20took%20his%20own%20photos%20of%20test%20subjects%2C%20rather%20than%20scraping%20the%20internet%20for%20self-posted%20photos.%20That%20enabled%20him%20to%20control%20for%20more%20variables%20%E2%80%94%20cutting%20out%20backdrops%2C%20keeping%20hairstyles%20the%20same%2C%20making%20sure%20people%20looked%20directly%20at%20the%20camera%20with%20a%20neutral%20expression.%20Then%2C%20using%20this%20new%20set%20of%20photos%2C%20he%20once%20again%20asked%20the%20algorithm%20to%20separate%20the%20conservatives%20from%20the%20liberals.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222700%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Two%20figures%20entrapped%20by%20a%20cage%20made%20of%20colorful%20tech%20modules%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F66aa4f2caab37011780bfb60%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%223495%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3E%3Cp%3EBrian%20Stauffer%20for%20BI%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20time%2C%20the%20machine%20did%20fractionally%20worse%20than%20humans%20at%20accurately%20predicting%20someone's%20political%20affiliation.%20And%20therein%20lies%20the%20problem.%20It's%20not%20just%20that%20Kosinski's%20central%20finding%20%E2%80%94%20that%20AI%20can%20read%20humans%20better%20than%20humans%20can%20%E2%80%94%20is%20very%20possibly%20wrong.%20It's%20that%20we'll%20tend%20to%20believe%20it%20anyway.%20Computation%2C%20the%20math%20that%20a%20machine%20has%20instead%20of%20a%20mind%2C%20%3Cem%3Eseems%3C%2Fem%3E%20objective%20and%20infallible%20%E2%80%94%20even%20if%20the%20computer%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Eis%20just%20operationalizing%20our%20own%20biases.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat%20faulty%20belief%20isn't%20just%20at%20the%20heart%20of%20science's%20misguided%20and%20terrifying%20attempts%20to%20measure%20human%20beings%20over%20the%20past%20three%20centuries.%20It's%20at%20the%20heart%20of%20the%20science%20itself.%20The%20way%20scientists%20know%20whether%20to%20believe%20they've%20found%20data%20that%20confirms%20a%20hypothesis%20is%20through%20statistics.%20And%20the%20pioneers%20of%20modern%20statistics%20%E2%80%94%20Francis%20Galton%2C%20Ronald%20Fisher%2C%20and%20Karl%20Pearson%20%E2%80%94%20were%20among%20the%20most%20egregious%20eugenicists%20and%20physiognomists%20of%20the%20late%2019th%20and%20early%2020th%20centuries.%20They%20believed%20that%20Black%20people%20were%20savages%2C%20that%20Jews%20were%20a%20gutter%20race%2C%20that%20only%20the%20%26quot%3Bright%26quot%3B%20kind%20of%20people%20should%20be%20allowed%20to%20have%20babies.%20As%20the%20mathematician%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fnautil.us%2Fhow-eugenics-shaped-statistics-238014%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3EAubrey%20Clayton%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20has%20argued%2C%20they%20literally%20invented%20statistical%20analysis%20to%20give%20their%20virulent%20racial%20prejudice%20a%20veneer%20of%20objectivity.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20methods%20and%20techniques%20they%20pioneered%20are%20with%20us%20today.%20They're%20behind%20IQ%20testing%20and%20college-admissions%20exams%2C%20the%20ceaseless%20racial%20profiling%20by%20police%2C%20the%20systems%20being%20used%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.hirevue.com%2Fcase-studies%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Escreen%20job%20candidates%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20for%20things%20like%20%26quot%3Bsoft%20skills%26quot%3B%20and%20%26quot%3Bgrowth%20mindset.%26quot%3B%20It's%20no%20coincidence%20that%20Hitler%20took%20his%20cues%20from%20the%20eugenicists%20%E2%80%94%20including%20an%20infamous%201929%20ruling%20by%20the%20US%20Supreme%20Court%20that%20upheld%20the%20forced%20sterilization%20of%20women%20deemed%20by%20science%20to%20be%20%26quot%3Bimbeciles.%26quot%3B%20Imagine%20what%20a%20second%20Trump%20administration%20would%20do%20with%20AI-driven%20facial%20recognition%20at%20a%20border%20crossing%20%E2%80%94%20or%20anywhere%2C%20really%2C%20with%20the%20goal%20of%20identifying%20%26quot%3Benemies%20of%20the%20state.%26quot%3B%20Such%20tools%2C%20in%20fact%2C%20are%20already%20built%20into%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.manufacturing.net%2Fvideo%2Fvideo%2F22914405%2Fautomatic-ammo-vending-machines-with-ai-begin-operating-at-grocery-stores%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Eammunition%20vending%20machines%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20(possibly%20one%20of%20the%20most%20dystopian%20phrases%20I%20have%20ever%20typed).%20They're%20also%20being%20incorporated%20into%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Emany%20of%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fdocs.google.com%2Fspreadsheets%2Fd%2F1EGXXJf9PCO79Q3KRl80aXTyL_QCsaZYy%2Fedit%3Fgid%3D1630889035%23gid%3D1630889035%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Etechnologies%20deployed%20on%20America's%20southern%20border%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20built%20by%20startups%20founded%20and%20funded%20by%20the%20same%20people%20supporting%20the%20Trump%20campaign.%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3EYou%20think%20racism%20is%20systemic%20now%3F%20Just%20wait%20until%20the%20system%20is%20literally%20programmed%20with%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20various%20technologies%20we've%20taken%20to%20calling%20%26quot%3Bartificial%20intelligence%26quot%3B%20are%20basically%20just%20statistical%20engines%20that%20have%20been%20trained%20on%20our%20biases.%20Kosinski%20thinks%20AI's%20ability%20to%20make%20the%20kind%20of%20personality%20judgments%20he%20studies%20will%20only%20get%20better.%20%26quot%3BUltimately%2C%20we're%20developing%20a%20model%20that%20produces%20outputs%20like%20a%20human%20mind%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20tells%20me.%20And%20once%20the%20machine%20has%20thoroughly%20studied%20and%20mastered%20our%20all-too-human%20prejudices%2C%20he%20believes%2C%20it%20will%20then%20be%20able%20to%20see%20into%20our%20minds%20and%20use%20whatever%20it%20finds%20there%20to%20call%20the%20shots.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20Kosinski's%20nightmare%2C%20this%20won't%20be%20Skynet%20bombing%20us%20into%20oblivion.%20The%20sophisticated%20AI%20of%20tomorrow%20will%20know%20us%20so%20well%20that%20it%20won't%20need%20force%20%E2%80%94%20it%20will%20simply%20ensure%20our%20compliance%20by%20giving%20us%20exactly%20what%20we%20want.%20%26quot%3BThink%20about%20having%20a%20model%20that%20has%20read%20all%20the%20books%20on%20the%20planet%2C%20knows%20you%20intimately%2C%20knows%20how%20to%20talk%20to%20you%2C%20and%20is%20rewarded%20not%20only%20by%20you%20but%20by%20billions%20of%20other%20people%20for%20engaging%20interactions%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20says.%20%26quot%3BIt%20will%20become%20a%20master%20manipulator%20%E2%80%94%20a%20master%20entertainment%20system.%26quot%3B%20That%20is%20the%20future%20Kosinski%20fears%20%E2%80%94%20even%20as%20he%20continues%20to%20tinker%20with%20the%20very%20models%20that%20prove%20it%20will%20come%20to%20pass.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fauthor%2Fadam-roge