2F%2Fwww.nhc.gov.cn%2Fxwzb%2Fwebcontroller.do%3Fmessagelist%3D1%26titleSeq%3D11164%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E807%20in%202020%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22http%3A%2F%2Fwww.nhc.gov.cn%2Fxcs%2Fs3574%2F202205%2F71ecabbcfa8f46ec920f1b7545cf02f0.shtml%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E793%20in%202021%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20am%20not%20very%20surprised%20to%20hear%20about%20Goldman%20Sachs'%20forecast%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcola.unh.edu%2Fperson%2Flin-zhang%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ELin%20Zhang%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20a%20University%20of%20New%20Hampshire%20professor%20who%20studies%20entrepreneurship%20and%20the%20digital%20economy%20in%20China.%20%26quot%3BWe%20could%20observe%20similar%20trends%20in%20early%20developed%20countries%20in%20Europe%20and%20East%20Asia.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22b891e1c2-604c-4314-bc24-f33d9a0946bf%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EPets%20provide%20'companionship'%20for%20younger%20Chinese%20people%20without%20the%20burden%20of%20childrearing%2C%20experts%20say%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EExperts%20say%20that%20there's%20a%20practical%20reason%20why%20the%20Chinese%20are%20opting%20for%20pets%20instead%20of%20children.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EZhang%20from%20University%20of%20New%20Hampshire%20said%20that%20pets%20play%20an%20important%20cultural%20role%20as%20companions%20to%20unmarried%20and%20childless%20youths%2C%20and%20seniors%20whose%20children%20don't%20live%20with%20them.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIn%20general%2C%20I%20think%20China's%20going%20through%20a%20cultural%20transformation%20related%20to%20its%20rising%20living%20standards%20that%20people%20start%20to%20find%20cultural%20meaning%20in%20pets%20instead%20of%20treating%20them%20more%20as%20functional%20animals%20like%20in%20traditional%20agricultural%20society%2C%26quot%3B%20Zhang%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EZheng%20Mu%2C%20an%20assistant%20professor%20of%20sociology%20and%20anthropology%20at%20the%20National%20University%20of%20Singapore%2C%20said%20pets%20also%20allow%20younger%20Chinese%20people%20to%20fulfill%20their%20%26quot%3Bneeds%20of%20meaningful%20companionship%20and%20intimacy%26quot%3B%20without%20%26quot%3Blong-term%20obligations%20such%20as%20the%20education%20of%20children.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ERaising%20pets%20instead%20of%20children%20is%20also%20a%20subtle%20way%20to%20deviate%20from%20social%20norms.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BBecause%20the%20obligations%20for%20children%20are%20more%20socially%20normative%20and%20constraining%2C%20and%20also%20more%20long%20term%2C%20but%20obligations%20for%20pets%20can%20be%20more%20individualistic%2C%26quot%3B%20Zheng%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22774ba749-2bdd-4b5c-a85c-48466bdff58f%5C%22%3ECash%20gifts%20and%20subsidies%20haven't%20stopped%20China's%20baby%20bust%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20ticking%20demographic%20time%20bomb%20has%20become%20a%20top%20concern%20for%20Chinese%20policymakers%2C%20who%20have%20pulled%20out%20all%20stops%20to%20arrest%20the%20decline%20in%20births.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBesides%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.brookings.edu%2Farticles%2Fthe-end-of-chinas-one-child-policy%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eaxing%20its%20controversial%20one-child%20policy%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20China%20has%20sought%20to%20encourage%20childbearing%20by%20dangling%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fchina-reward-cash-bride-25-years-marriage-babies-population-2023-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ecash%20gifts%20to%20newly%20married%20couples%3C%2Fa%3E%20as%20well%20as%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fchina-population-demographics-birthrate-fertility-subsidies-incentives-ivf-betrothal-gift-2023-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Esubsidies%20for%20fertility%20treatments%20and%20childcare%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20the%20incentives%20don't%20seem%20to%20have%20changed%20the%20minds%20of%20Chinese%20women%2C%20who%20told%20Business%20Insider%20in%20February%20that%20they%20were%20turned%20off%20by%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwomen-china-not-having-kids-tell-us-why-2024-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ehefty%20financial%20costs%3C%2Fa%3E%20of%20starting%20a%20family.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BLet's%20face%20it%2C%20having%20a%20child%20is%20like%20owning%20an%20investment%20with%20no%20guaranteed%20return%20for%20at%20least%2018%20years%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Chinese%20venture%20capital%20analyst%20Bihan%20Chen%2C%2026%2C%20told%20BI.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EContent%20creator%20Emily%20Huang%2C%2029%2C%20told%20BI%20that%20the%20biggest%20thing%20on%20her%20mind%20right%20now%20is%20how%20she's%20going%20to%20fund%20her%20own%20retirement.%20Having%20children%2C%20she%20said%2C%20would%20make%20that%20goal%20even%20more%20distant.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20wouldn't%20choose%20to%20spend%20a%20part%20of%20my%20income%20on%20children%20because%20it's%20expensive%2C%26quot%3B%20Huang%20said.%20%26quot%3BI%20feel%20like%20with%20my%20current%20level%20of%20income%2C%20I%20can't%20retire%20comfortably%20anytime%20soon.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%2201936a53-633d-4353-9779-f67125c45bb0%5C%22%3EThe%20boom%20in%20pet%20spending%20is%20not%20just%20a%20China-only%20phenomenon%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3ETo%20be%20sure%2C%20China%20is%20not%20the%20only%20country%20that%20is%20expected%20to%20see%20a%20boost%20in%20pet-related%20expenditure.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20US%2C%20more%20households%20have%20pets%20than%20children.%20According%20to%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nar.realtor%2Fblogs%2Feconomists-outlook%2Fa-stunning-stat-there-are-more-american-households-with-pets-than-children%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E2023%20report%3C%2Fa%3E%20by%20the%20National%20Association%20of%20Realtors%20(NAR)%2C%2040%25%20of%20American%20households%20had%20children%20in%202022%2C%20down%20from%2048%25%20in%202002.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20contrast%2C%20pet%20ownership%20has%20increased%2C%20particularly%20since%20the%20COVID-19%20pandemic.%20The%20NAR%20report%20states%20that%2070%25%20of%20American%20households%20owned%20a%20pet%20in%202022%2C%20up%20from%2056%25%20in%201988.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20March%202023%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bloomberg.com%2Fcompany%2Fpress%2Fglobal-pet-industry-to-grow-to-500-billion-by-2030-bloomberg-intelligence-finds%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EBloomberg%20Intelligence%3C%2Fa%3E%20published%20its%20Pet%20Economy%20Report%2C%20which%20forecasts%20that%20the%20global%20pet%20industry%20is%20expected%20to%20increase%20in%20size%20from%20%24320%20billion%20to%20%24500%20billion%20by%202030%20as%20the%20worldwide%20pet%20population%20continues%20to%20grow.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20the%20report's%20authors%2C%20the%20surge%20in%20spending%20isn't%20solely%20due%20to%20an%20increase%20in%20pets%20per%20se%20but%20also%20because%20pets%20are%20living%20longer.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIncreased%20pet%20nutrition%20is%20leading%20to%20longer%20pet%20lives%20around%20the%20world%2C%26quot%3B%20Ann-Hunter%20van%20Kirk%2C%20a%20senior%20biopharmaceutical%20analyst%20at%20Bloomberg%20Intelligence%2C%20said%20in%20a%20statement%20about%20the%20report.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWith%20this%20comes%20an%20increased%20need%20for%20spending%20relating%20to%20expensive%20healthcare%20for%20aging%20pets%2C%20and%20we%20project%20that%20this%20spending%20on%20lasting%20health%20for%20pets%20will%20continue%20to%20swell%20over%20the%20next%20decade%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20continued.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fgoldman-sachs-china-city-dwellers-rather-raise-pets-than-toddlers-2024-8%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1722844077000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F66b03f13a5247369a3e96163%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%