%20shocked%E2%80%99%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThrough%20Talking%20Fingers%2C%20Padma%20and%20Chitra%20have%20given%20a%20voice%20to%2032%20young%20minds%20who%20felt%20imprisoned%20by%20their%20inability%20to%20express%20themselves%20through%20speech.%20With%20this%20newfound%20voice%2C%20many%20of%20them%20say%20it%20has%20opened%20up%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthebetterindia.com%2F304033%2Fmumbai-friends-launch-mann-centre-for-jobs-for-people-with-intellectual-disabilities%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ea%20world%20of%20possibilities%3C%2Fa%3E.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFor%20instance%2C%2031-year-old%20Soumya%20Upadhyay%20from%20West%20Bengal%20found%20a%20medium%20through%20which%20he%20could%20articulate%20the%20harrowing%20time%20he%20had%20experienced%20during%20his%20childhood%3B%20the%20effect%20of%20multiple%20seizures%20throughout%20the%20day.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHow%20does%20it%20feel%20to%20write%20down%20everything%20you%20cannot%20say%20out%20loud%3F%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CLike%20being%20able%20to%20climb%20a%20high%20mountain%2C%E2%80%9D%20says%2016-year-old%20Aadi%20Narayanan%20Nair.%20It%20took%20Aadi%20six%20years%20to%20learn%20how%20to%20type%20%E2%80%94%20he%20credits%20a%20very%20patient%20mother%20for%20this.%20Today%2C%20words%20are%20his%20best%20friend.%C2%A0%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-heading%5C%22%3E%E2%80%98Our%20sensory%20world%20is%20different%20from%20yours%E2%80%99%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthebetterindia.com%2F252386%2Fatypical-online-job-portal-job-seekers-disabilities-covid-19-pandemic-vineet-saraiwala-autism-down-syndrome-learning-disability-hearing-impairment-gop94%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EPeople%20with%20autism%3C%2Fa%3E%20tend%20to%20have%20heightened%20senses%3B%20their%20nerves%20are%20attuned%20to%20subtle%20sounds.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ELetting%20us%20into%20their%20worlds%2C%20Ahan%20Sengupta%20shares%20one%20of%20his%20biggest%20fears%20%E2%80%94%20cutting%20his%20nails.%20%E2%80%9CFor%20the%20longest%20time%2C%20I%20thought%20they%20were%20a%20part%20of%20my%20body%20and%20that%20I%20would%20be%20hurting%20myself%20if%20I%20cut%20them.%E2%80%9D%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20same%20fear%20gripped%20him%20when%20it%20came%20to%20injections.%20Elaborating%20on%20the%20paranoia%20that%20sometimes%20engulfs%20him%2C%20he%20says%2C%20%E2%80%9CPeople%20with%20autism%20always%20feel%20that%20something%20will%20be%20snatched%20from%20them.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAhan%20and%20his%20co-authors%20agree%20that%20shrill%20noises%2C%20bright%20lights%2C%20and%20people%20taking%20their%20pictures%20are%20huge%20stressors.%20As%2019-year-old%20Navneet%20Kulkarni%20shares%2C%20%E2%80%9CMy%20mind%20is%20like%20a%20shopping%20mall%20full%20of%20crowds%2C%20different%20music%2C%20too%20many%20shops%2C%20too%20many%20bright%20lights%2C%20aromatic%20smells%3B%20all%20my%20senses%20get%20so%20distracted%20with%20so%20many%20things%20in%20my%20surroundings.%E2%80%9D%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-heading%5C%22%3E%E2%80%98Stimming%20makes%20us%20feel%20comfortable%E2%80%99%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EShort%20for%20self-stimulating%20behaviour%20%E2%80%94%20stimming%20refers%20to%20doing%20an%20action%20over%20and%20over%20or%20repeating%20the%20same%20sound%20several%20times.%20A%20coping%20mechanism%20is%20how%2018-year-old%20Aarav%20Krishnatheeram%20describes%20it%20to%20be.%20Life%20is%20tough%20without%20it%2C%20he%20notes.%20While%20for%20Aarav%2C%20the%20stimming%20involves%20actions%20like%20shouting%20and%20rocking%20himself%2C%20for%20Navneet%20it%20means%20moving%20his%20fingers%20up%20and%20down.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CSometimes%20my%20behaviour%20may%20look%20funny%20to%20people%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20says%2C%20adding%20that%20it%20provides%20him%20recourse%20when%20he%20is%20in%20a%20high-activity%20zone.%20%E2%80%9CWhen%20I%20go%20out%2C%20all%20the%20surroundings%20distract%20my%20vision%2C%20it%20feels%20like%20my%20body%20is%20flying%20and%20my%20head%20is%20banging.%20To%20balance%20my%20sensory%20system%20I%20do%20stimming.%20I%20feel%20safe%20and%20comfortable%20when%20I%20fidget%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20explains.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-heading%5C%22%3E%E2%80%98Don%E2%80%99t%20treat%20us%20like%20we%20don%E2%80%99t%20exist%E2%80%99%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20Chitra%E2%80%99s%20son%2C%20Tarun%20Paul%20Mathew%20(17)%2C%20the%20saddest%20reality%20is%20losing%20one%E2%80%99s%20identity.%20%E2%80%9CThis%20is%20true%20for%20many%20of%20us%20non-speaking%20autistics%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20notes.%20But%20writing%2C%20he%20says%2C%20has%20helped%20position%20him%20and%20other%20neurodivergent%20individuals%20(who%20are%20unable%20to%20communicate%20through%20speech)%20on%20the%20same%20level%20playing%20field%20as%20their%20neurotypical%20counterparts.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-image%5C%22%3E%5Cn%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20500px)%20100vw%2C%20500px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F07%2FWhatsApp-Image-2024-07-02-at-6.19.32-PM_11zon-1721808799-500x750.jpeg%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22500%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Chitra%20Paul%2C%20co-editor%20of%20Talking%20Fingers%2C%20with%20her%20son%20Tarun%20Paul%20Mathew%2C%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F07%2FWhatsApp-Image-2024-07-02-at-6.19.32-PM_11zon-1721808799-500x750.jpeg%20500w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F07%2FWhatsApp-Image-2024-07-02-at-6.19.32-PM_11zon-1721808799-200x300.jpeg%20200w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F07%2FWhatsApp-Image-2024-07-02-at-6.19.32-PM_11zon-1721808799-768x1152.jpeg%20768w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F0